name: chrome_app
comment: A library to expose the Chrome app APIs.

class.name: AlarmCreateInfo
class.preview: todo(mpcomplete): rename to CreateInfo when http://crbug.com/123073 is fixed.

class.name: WindowType
class.preview: 'shell' is the default window type. 'panel' is managed by the OS (Currently experimental, Ash only).

class.name: State
class.preview: State of a window: normal, fullscreen, maximized, minimized.

class.name: _ChromeAppWindow
class.preview: Use the chrome.app.window API to create windows. Windows have an optional frame with title bar and size controls. They are not associated with any Chrome browser windows.

class.name: LaunchData
class.preview: Optional data for the launch. Either items, or the pair (url, referrerUrl) can be present for any given launch.

class.name: ChromeAppRuntime
class.preview: Use the chrome.app.runtime API to manage the app lifecycle. The app runtime manages app installation, controls the event page, and can shut down the app at anytime.

class.name: GetInfoResult
class.preview: The return type for getInfo.

class.name: StartDiscoveryOptions
class.preview: Options for the startDiscovery function.

class.name: SetOutOfBandPairingDataOptions
class.preview: Options for the setOutOfBandPairingData function.

class.name: WriteOptions
class.preview: Options for the write function.

class.name: ReadOptions
class.preview: Options for the read function.

class.name: DisconnectOptions
class.preview: Options for the disconnect function.

class.name: ConnectOptions
class.preview: Options for the connect function.

class.name: GetServicesOptions
class.preview: Options for the getServices function.

class.name: GetProfilesOptions
class.preview: Options for the getProfiles function.

class.name: GetDevicesOptions
class.preview: Options for the getDevices function. If chrome/chrome_app.GetDevicesOptions.profile is not provided, all devices known to the system are returned.

class.name: OnClickData
class.preview: Information sent when a context menu item is clicked.

class.name: OnClickedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a context menu item is clicked.

class.name: UrlFilter
class.preview: Filters URLs for various criteria. See event filtering. All criteria are case sensitive.

class.name: ChromeEvent
class.preview: An object which allows the addition and removal of listeners for a Chrome event.

class.name: Rule
class.preview: Description of a declarative rule for handling events.

class.name: ChooseEntryResult
class.preview: The return type for chooseEntry.

class.name: WatchLocationRequestInfo
class.preview: Parameter of watchLocation call.

class.name: Location
class.preview: Parameter of onLocationUpdate event's listener.

class.name: Coordinates
class.preview: Coordinates part of the Location object.

class.name: RequestUpdateCheckResult
class.preview: The return type for requestUpdateCheck.

class.name: MessageSender
class.preview: An object containing information about the script context that sent a message or request.

class.name: Port
class.preview: An object which allows two way communication with other pages.

class.name: OnMessageExternalEvent
class.preview: Fired when a message is sent from another extension/app. Cannot be used in a content script.

class.name: OnMessageEvent
class.preview: Fired when a message is sent from either an extension process or a content script.

class.name: SerialReceiveErrorInfo
class.preview: Data from an onReceiveError event.

class.name: SerialReceiveInfo
class.preview: Data from an onReceive event.

class.name: DeviceControlSignals
class.preview: The set of control signals which may be set by a connected serial device. These can be queried using getControlSignals. Note that support for these signals is device-dependent.

class.name: HostControlSignals
class.preview: The set of control signals which may be sent to a connected serial device using setControlSignals. Note that support for these signals is device-dependent.

class.name: ConnectionInfo
class.preview: Result of the getInfo method.

class.name: ChromeSocketsUdp
class.preview: Use the chrome.sockets.udp API to send and receive data over the network using UDP connections. This API supersedes the UDP functionality previously found in the "socket" API. Note that the socket ids created from this namespace are not compatible with ids created in other namespaces.

class.name: AcceptErrorInfo
class.preview: Data from an onAcceptError event.

class.name: AcceptInfo
class.preview: Data from an onAccept event.

class.name: ChromeSocketsTcpServer
class.preview: Use the chrome.sockets.tcpServer API to create server applications using TCP connections. This API supersedes the TCP functionality previously found in the chrome.socket API. Note that the socket ids created from this namespace are not compatible with ids created in other namespaces.

class.name: ReceiveErrorInfo
class.preview: Data from an onReceiveError event.

class.name: ReceiveInfo
class.preview: Data from an onReceive event.

class.name: SocketInfo
class.preview: Result of the getInfo method.

class.name: SendInfo
class.preview: Result of the send method.

class.name: CreateInfo
class.preview: Result of create call.

class.name: SocketProperties
class.preview: The socket properties specified in the create or update function. Each property is optional. If a property value is not specified, a default value is used when calling create, or the existing value if preserved when calling update.

class.name: ChromeSocketsTcp
class.preview: Use the chrome.sockets.tcp API to send and receive data over the network using TCP connections. This API supersedes the TCP functionality previously found in the chrome.socket API. Note that the socket ids created from this namespace are not compatible with ids created in other namespaces.

class.name: StorageOnChangedEvent
class.preview: Fired when one or more items change.

class.name: ChromeSystemStorage
class.preview: Use the chrome.system.storage API to query storage device information and be notified when a removable storage device is attached and detached.

class.name: ChromeSystemNetwork
class.preview: Use the chrome.system.network API.

class.name: ChromeSystemMemory
class.preview: The chrome.system.memory API.

class.name: ChromeSystemDisplay
class.preview: Use the system.display API to query display metadata.

class.name: ChromeSystemCpu
class.preview: Use the system.cpu API to query CPU metadata.

class.name: TtsVoice
class.preview: A description of a voice available for speech synthesis.

class.name: TtsEvent
class.preview: An event from the TTS engine to communicate the status of an utterance.

class.name: ChromeSetting
class.preview: An interface that allows access to a Chrome browser setting. See proxy.settings for an example.

class.name: EnumerateDevicesAndRequestAccessOptions
class.preview: Describes the properties of devices which are found via findDevices.

class.name: EnumerateDevicesOptions
class.preview: Describes the properties of devices which are found via getDevices.

class.name: IsochronousTransferInfo
class.preview: IsochronousTransferInfo describes a single multi-packet isochronous transfer.

class.name: GenericTransferInfo
class.preview: GenericTransferInfo is used by both bulk and interrupt transfers to specify the parameters of the transfer.

class.name: ControlTransferInfo
class.preview: ControlTransferInfo represents that parameters to a single USB control transfer.

class.name: ConnectionHandle
class.preview: Returned by openDevice to be used for USB communication. Every time a device is opened, a new connection handle is created.

class.name: Device
class.preview: Returned by getDevices to identify a connected USB device.

class.name: SynchronizationType
class.preview: For isochronous mode, SynchronizationType and UsageType map to their namesakes within the USB specification.

class.name: Direction
class.preview: Direction, Recipient, RequestType, and TransferType all map to their namesakes within the USB specification.

class.name: ChromeEnum
class.preview: The abstract superclass of Chrome enums.

class.name: ChromeApi
class.preview: A common super class for the Chrome APIs.

class.name: ChromeObject
class.preview: The abstract superclass of objects that can hold chrome/dart-js.JsObject proxies.
